title: Area Volleyball: United sweeps Stark County
text: Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 10:03 PM Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 10:03 PM MONMOUTH — The United High School volleyball team defeated Lincoln Trail Conference rival Stark County 25-14, 25-19 on Tuesday. Lauren Sperry led the Red Storm (24-3) with nine kills and a block. Rachel Watson had four digs, Emma Marshall served two aces and Mallory Flynn gave out 11 assists for United. West Central def. ROWVA 25-5, 25-14 At Oneida, Whitney Finley served 12 points and had eight digs to lead the Heat past the Tigers in a LTC contest. Danyel McKune had seven kills and seven blocks, Kendra Spiker made six kills, seven digs and served three aces, Somer Hill dished out 19 assists and Katie Droste had three aces for West Central. ROWVA was led by Jordan Maher with five digs. Madi Kalb had three kills and Kayla Baumgardner gave out seven assists. Havana def. Bushnell-PC 25-21, 25-22 At Bushnell, the Spartans fell to the Ducks in straight sets in a Prairieland Conference match. Kayley Peck served 18 points, including nine aces, to lead Bushnell-Prairie City (6-17, 2-6). Stephanie Beaird had five kills, Logan Brown had 15 digs and Tiffany Slater gave out 12 assists for the Spartans. Princeville def. Galva 25-19, 25-14 At Princeville, the Wildcats could not recover from a first match loss to loss to the Princes’ in straight sets. Laurin Hopping led Galva in the LTC matchup with four kills, five service points and six digs. Sarah Jeffries added six digs and Greta Rux gave out six assists for Galva. The Register-Mail
